# Dashboard (React)

Create React App + TypeScript. UI: React Bootstrap + styled-components. State: Redux Toolkit + RTK Query.

## Structure

```
pages/        Route-level views (HomePage, DashboardPage, admin/*)
components/   Reusable UI (common/, subscriptions/, dashboard/, layout/)
constants/    Shared config (e.g. serverNav.ts for dashboard server shell)
store/        Redux slices + RTK Query API modules (store/api/)
types/        Shared interfaces (ISettings, IServer, User, …)
helpers/      Hooks, theme, Discord/Stripe utilities
```

## Server dashboard layout

Server-scoped routes (`/dashboard/:serverId/*`) use a shared shell:

- [`constants/serverNav.ts`](dashboard/src/constants/serverNav.ts) — grouped nav sections, item metadata (path, name, icon, description), and `getServerNavItem()`
- [`components/dashboard/server/ServerLayout.tsx`](dashboard/src/components/dashboard/server/ServerLayout.tsx) — sidebar + page header + outlet wrapper
- [`components/dashboard/server/ServerPageHeader.tsx`](dashboard/src/components/dashboard/server/ServerPageHeader.tsx) — page title row with nav icon and premium badge
- Mobile server nav opens from [`Header.tsx`](dashboard/src/components/common/Header.tsx) (`HeaderServerNavButton` next to the logo) via [`helpers/serverNavMobile.tsx`](dashboard/src/helpers/serverNavMobile.tsx); offcanvas lives in `ServerLayout`
- Desktop: sticky grouped sidebar; mobile: Offcanvas nav from header menu button
- Layout/nav tokens live in [`helpers/theme.ts`](dashboard/src/helpers/theme.ts) (`layout`, `nav`, `layout.padding`, `layout.breakpoints`)

## Site header

[`components/common/Header.tsx`](dashboard/src/components/common/Header.tsx) + [`Header/styles.tsx`](dashboard/src/components/common/Header/styles.tsx) — global navbar with theme-aligned surface, compact logo, pill user menu, polished mobile collapse nav, and `HeaderServerNavButton` on server dashboard routes

Add or rename server sub-routes in `serverNav.ts` and `routes.tsx` together.

## Home page

[`pages/home/HomePage.tsx`](dashboard/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx) — landing page with hero (invite + login/dashboard CTAs, screenshot carousel), feature grid, and bottom CTA band. [`HeroScreenshotCarousel.tsx`](dashboard/src/pages/home/HeroScreenshotCarousel.tsx) is the themed Bootstrap carousel in the hero right column; slide clicks open a custom fullscreen lightbox (fade + zoom in, not Bootstrap modal slide) with prev/next controls. [`HeroInviteButton.tsx`](dashboard/src/pages/home/HeroInviteButton.tsx) is the gold-gradient Discord invite CTA (Discord icon badge, hint line, arrow hover). Styled components and feature metadata live in [`pages/home/styles.ts`](dashboard/src/pages/home/styles.ts) and [`pages/home/features.ts`](dashboard/src/pages/home/features.ts) — mirrors dashboard server nav (track, kills, assists, deaths, juicy, battles, rankings) plus regional support, recent kill-image features (NEW), dashboard, and premium; uses theme gold accents consistent with header and subscription cards. Home route uses transparent [`HomePaper`](dashboard/src/styles/App.tsx) so the ambient background is visible. [`AmbientPageShell.tsx`](dashboard/src/components/layout/AmbientPageShell.tsx) + [`ambientBackgroundStyles.ts`](dashboard/src/components/layout/ambientBackgroundStyles.ts) — shared animated ambient background (wallpaper drift, aurora mesh, glow orbs, grid, noise, vignette); used by Home and Premium pages. `HomeBackground` layers a faint wallpaper, color mesh (gold/Europe/Americas), animated orbs, grid, noise, and vignette behind `HomeContent`. Logged-in hero CTA uses `HeroDashboardLink` (avatar, username hint, gold-bordered card button). Logged-out secondary CTA uses [`HeroLoginButton.tsx`](dashboard/src/pages/home/HeroLoginButton.tsx) (same size/layout as dashboard link).

## Content panel

[`components/layout/ContentPanel.tsx`](dashboard/src/components/layout/ContentPanel.tsx) — shared elevated surface (`ContentPanelRoot`) used by global [`Page.tsx`](dashboard/src/components/Page.tsx) and extended by server [`styles.ts`](dashboard/src/components/dashboard/server/styles.ts) for track/settings-specific nested rules.

## Unsaved changes bar

[`UnsavedChangesBar.tsx`](dashboard/src/components/dashboard/UnsavedChangesBar.tsx) — sticky bottom bar when there are pending edits. Used by [`Settings.tsx`](dashboard/src/components/Settings.tsx) (all server settings pages) and [`TrackPage.tsx`](dashboard/src/pages/dashboard/server/TrackPage.tsx). Settings dirty state uses `settings.changed` in the settings slice; no full-page loader on save.

